11 An Act relating to The Plumbing License Law of 1955;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Sections 1003 and 1017, which
12 relate to definitions and inapplicability; defining
term; adding exceptions to applicability of certain
13 provisions; updating statutory language; updating
statutory reference; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1003, is
18 amended to read as follows:
19 Section 1003. As used in The Plumbing License Law of 1955:
20 1. "Board" means the Construction Industries Board;
21 2. "Committee" means the Oklahoma State Committee of Plumbing
22 Examiners appointed by the Construction Industries Board;
23 3. "Plumbing Hearing Board" means the State Plumbing Hearing
24 Board which shall consist of a designee of the Construction
SB1035 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Indu stries Board, as chair, and the members of the Oklahoma State
2 Committee of Plumbing Examiners;
3 4. "Apprentice" or "plumber's apprentice" means any person
4 sixteen (16) years of age or older who, as the principal occupation
5 of the person, is engaged in learning and assisting in the
6 installation of plumbing under the direct supervision of a licensed
7 journeyman plumber or plumbing contractor;
8 5. "Journeyman plumber" means any person other than a master
9 plumber or plumbing contractor who engages in or works at the actual
10 installation, alteration, repair and/or, or renovation of plumbing;
11 6. "Temporary journeyman plumber" means any person other than a
12 person permanently licensed as a journeyman plumber, master plumber,
13 or plumbing contractor in this state who meets the temporary
14 licensure requirements of Section 1006.1 of this title;
15 7. "Master plumber" is a term used and defined under laws which
16 have been repealed. A person formerly known as a master plumber is
17 henceforth to be known as a "plumbing contractor" as defined in this
18 section;
19 8. "Plumbing contractor" means any person who is skilled in the
20 planning, superintending, and practical installation of plumbing and
21 who is familiar with the laws and rules governing the same. This
22 definition may be construed to mean any person who has qualified and
23 is licensed under The Plumbing License Law of 1955 as a plumbing
24 contractor, who may operate as an individual, a firm, partnership,
SB1035 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 limi ted liability company, or corporation, or other legal entity to
2 engage in the business of plumbing, or the business of contracting
3 to do plumbing, or furnish labor or materials or both for the
4 installation, repair, maintenance, or renovation of plumbing
5 according to the requirements of The Plumbing License Law of 1955.
6 Any former master plumber shall be known as a plumbing contractor;
7 9. 8. "Plumbing" means, and includes:
8 a. all piping, fixtures, appurtenances, and appliances
9 for, and in connection with, a supply of water within
10 or adjacent to any building, structure, or conveyance,
11 on the premises and to the connection with a water
12 main or other source of supply,
13 b. all piping, fixtures, appurtenances, and appliances
14 for sanitary drainage or storm drainage facilities,
15 including venting systems for such facilities, within
16 or adjacent to any building, structure, or conveyance,
17 on the premises and to the connection with a public
18 disposal system or other acceptable terminal,
19 c. the installation, repair, maintenance, and renovation
20 of all piping, fixtures, appurtenances, and appliances
21 for a supply of water, or for the disposal of waste
22 water wastewater, liquid waste, or sewage within or
23 adjacent to any building, structure, or conveyance, on
24
